---
description: Standards for AI/LLM to Amazon Bedrock migration artifacts
alwaysApply: true
---

bedrock-migration-standards:

- Use the Bedrock Converse API as the default rewrite target; reach for provider-specific or InvokeModel paths only when Converse cannot express the call.
- Never change user-visible behavior silently: surface parameter-surface differences (e.g. temperature ranges, dropped penalties) as explicit decisions for the user to confirm.
- Validate target model IDs against the account's live inference profiles before use; only an exact match auto-resolves.
- Emit least-privilege IAM guidance scoped to the selected model and inference-profile ARNs, never wildcard Bedrock permissions.
- Evaluate output quality against a golden dataset before declaring the migration done; cap evaluation volume and warn the user about cost before any paid Bedrock calls.
- Deliver changes on a dedicated git branch and never push to a remote on the user's behalf.
